{
  "texts": [
    "Observe that the number of surjections is given by, |surj(𝑖, 𝑗)| = 𝑗!𝑆 (𝑖, 𝑗), where 𝑆 (𝑖, 𝑗) is the Stirling number of the second kind.",
    "In the computation of 𝐻 -1 we make use of the fact that the inverse of 𝐻 exists since none of the diagonal elements 𝐻 𝑘,𝑘 = |surj(𝑘, 𝑘)| = 𝑘! are zero.",
    "Since 𝐻 is lower triangular, we have that 𝐻 -1 is also lower triangular, and that the diagonal elements of 𝐻 -1 are the reciprocal of the diagonal elements of 𝐻.",
    "The terms away from the leading diagonal may be computed iteratively, simply using the equation 𝐻 -1 𝐻 = 𝐼.",
    "In particular, we see that the \"top idempotent\" corresponding to [𝑑] ∈ Epi ≤𝑑 is given by𝑒 𝑑 = 1 𝑑!"
  ]
}